  user_input {
    user_response: "Review my Spotify Discovery Boost prototype and improve it from a Product Manager and UX Designer perspective.\n\nContext:\nDiscovery Boost is a proposed Spotify feature that helps long-term users discover fresh songs without leaving their preferred music taste.\n\nCurrent Flow:\n\n1. User is listening to music.\n2. Spotify detects repetitive listening behavior.\n3. A prompt appears:\n    \342\200\234You\342\200\231ve been enjoying the same tracks lately. Want to discover fresh songs with a similar vibe?\342\200\235\n4. User can choose:\n    * Try Discovery Boost\n    * Not Now\n5. If enabled, Spotify inserts a few new songs into the existing queue.\n6. New songs are marked with a \342\200\234\342\234\250 New\342\200\235 tag.\n7. If the user likes a discovered song, a success state appears.\n\nI want you to:\n\n1. Critique the feature like a Senior Product Manager at Spotify.\n2. Identify UX weaknesses and friction points.\n3. Suggest improvements to the trigger, messaging, onboarding, and queue experience.\n4. Recommend better microcopy for all user-facing text.\n5. Suggest how Spotify could explain why a song was recommended (e.g., \342\200\234Added because you like M83\342\200\235).\n6. Improve trust, transparency, and user control.\n7. Suggest additional screens or interactions if needed.\n8. Evaluate whether this feels like a real Spotify feature or a student project.\n9. Suggest metrics Spotify should track if this feature were launched.\n10. Provide a revised end-to-end user flow that feels production-ready.\n\nBe highly critical and realistic. Act like a Senior Product Manager and Senior UX Designer reviewing a feature before launch.\n"
    items {
      text: "Review my Spotify Discovery Boost prototype and improve it from a Product Manager and UX Designer perspective.\n\nContext:\nDiscovery Boost is a proposed Spotify feature that helps long-term users discover fresh songs without leaving their preferred music taste.\n\nCurrent Flow:\n\n1. User is listening to music.\n2. Spotify detects repetitive listening behavior.\n3. A prompt appears:\n    \342\200\234You\342\200\231ve been enjoying the same tracks lately. Want to discover fresh songs with a similar vibe?\342\200\235\n4. User can choose:\n    * Try Discovery Boost\n    * Not Now\n5. If enabled, Spotify inserts a few new songs into the existing queue.\n6. New songs are marked with a \342\200\234\342\234\250 New\342\200\235 tag.\n7. If the user likes a discovered song, a success state appears.\n\nI want you to:\n\n1. Critique the feature like a Senior Product Manager at Spotify.\n2. Identify UX weaknesses and friction points.\n3. Suggest improvements to the trigger, messaging, onboarding, and queue experience.\n4. Recommend better microcopy for all user-facing text.\n5. Suggest how Spotify could explain why a song was recommended (e.g., \342\200\234Added because you like M83\342\200\235).\n6. Improve trust, transparency, and user control.\n7. Suggest additional screens or interactions if needed.\n8. Evaluate whether this feels like a real Spotify feature or a student project.\n9. Suggest metrics Spotify should track if this feature were launched.\n10. Provide a revised end-to-end user flow that feels production-ready.\n\nBe highly critical and realistic. Act like a Senior Product Manager and Senior UX Designer reviewing a feature before launch.\n"
    }
    media {
      mime_type: "text/html"
      blobref {
        blob_id: "/blobstore/prod/makersuite/spanner_managed/global::000054e2ea70026d:0000015f:2:000054e2ea70026d:0000000000000001::6c23c15644e5c136:0000020e12d018bc:000654ff57763aaf"
      }
      uri: "spotify-discovery-boost.html"
    }
