    thinking: "**Analyzing the Data**\n\nI\'ve begun reading the system instructions and related documentation, focusing on design, file structure, and available tools. I\'m building a mental model of the system\'s capabilities to align with the Spotify Discovery Boost prototype request. Now I\'m ready to move into focusing on the prototype request.\n\n\n**Refining the Approach**\n\nI\'m now integrating the user\'s HTML mockup into a React + Vite application, focusing on adhering to the framework guidelines. My priority is modularity; ensuring the code is split into manageable files and using the specified libraries, particularly lucide-react for icons and motion for transitions. The provided HTML, while complete, will be refactored to align with React\'s component structure.\n\n\n**Evaluating Skill Relevance**\n\nI\'ve categorized the available skills, marking each as relevant or not. Firebase and Gemini APIs seem unnecessary initially, but Gemini could enhance interactivity. I will now integrate skill-based enhancements into my mental model, allowing the system to use the prototype to self-explain. I will use the app itself to do the critique/assessment, instead of a separate review dashboard.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will start by reviewing the existing project files to see the current dependencies, setup, and structure so I can build a polished Spotify Discovery Boost prototype and PM/UX review dashboard. Let\'s inspect `package.json` and `metadata.json`."
