  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Designing the Applet**\n\nOkay, I\'ve got a solid grasp on the user\'s request. My focus is now on the applet\'s design and how to approach the task. It\'s time to critique this feature like a Senior Product Manager at Spotify, looking for UX weaknesses and friction points, which will be essential in the next steps. I\'m formulating a good framework to get started.\n\n\n**Refining the Dashboard**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on the dashboard format. My aim is to create an exceptionally impressive, high-fidelity, and easily digestible presentation. I\'m building a split-screen, interactive dashboard, with a toggleable left-side panel showcasing a Spotify Player & Queue Prototype. This will allow users to compare the current flow (original mockup) to the revised end-to-end production-ready flow, highlighting weaknesses and improvements.\n\n\n**Constructing the Prototype**\n\nI\'m deep in crafting the revised production-ready flow prototype. It\'s becoming incredibly authentic, with realistic cover art and smooth animations using `motion`. I\'m building out interactive components like the Spotify player, queue, and detailed opt-out settings. Plus, I am focusing on microcopy refinements and the addition of trust-building onboarding cards.\n\n**Developing the Review Console**\n\nNow, I\'m working on the right-side review console. It\'s structured as a Senior PM & Lead UX Designer Review Console, neatly tabbed to cover all user requirements. The goal is to provide elegant typography, metrics boards, interactive critiques, microcopy revisions, and in-depth trade-off analyses within the review console.\n\n\n**Analyzing the Experience**\n\nI am now performing a UX teardown, pinpointing friction points like the intrusive alerts and lack of user control, with interactive annotations on the player. I\'m focusing on the production-ready upgrades, including onboarding improvements and microcopy revisions using \"Before vs. After\" tables, along with recommendation rationales and trust features. I am now working on beautiful dashboards that show the exact KPI metrics Spotify would track. The updated dashboards now include mock interactive charts. I\'m also preparing a revised flow spec to chart how the production-ready feature runs.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will view `/src/index.css` to ensure it imports Tailwind CSS correctly, and then import the necessary fonts and styles for our Spotify interface and dashboard."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 5
      nanos: 633170512
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
