          text: "    analysis: `Users are inherently skeptical of algorithmic recommendations. If a random song plays, their default assumption is that Spotify\'s label contracts are pushing payola."
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "Adding a generic \"\342\234\250 New\" tag increases this suspicion because it provides zero context."
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "Showing the recommendation rationale (e.g., \"Added because you like M83\") transforms the song from an intruder into a welcome relative.`,"
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "    recommendation: `Introduce the \"Recommendation Rationale Capsule\" directly below the track title in the Queue and inside the Now Playing view."
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "Utilize three tiered levels of rationale:"
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "- **Direct Seed Connection**: \"Similar to *Midnight City*\" (for high-similarity fits)."
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "- **Aesthetic Vibe Match**: \"Matches the upbeat synth of *MGMT*\" (for style-based fits)."
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "- **Social Proofing**: \"Trending with listeners who enjoy *Daft Punk*\" (for popularity-based fits).`"
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "  },"
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "  {"
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "    id: \'crit-5\',"
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "    title: \'5. Improving Trust, Control, and Transparency\',"
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "    description: \'Empowering the user to guide the algorithm rather than being subject to it.\',"
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "    rating: \'critical\',"
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "    analysis: `The current flow operates on a simple binary: Enable or Disable. Once enabled, the algorithm operates as a black box. This is the fastest way to drive users to disable the feature forever."
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "In a real product environment, taste is highly dynamic. A user might want a \"Light Refresh\" (10% new songs) vs. a \"Deep Exploration\" (40% new songs), or they might want to exclude certain genres entirely.`,"
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "    recommendation: `Implement three critical Trust and Control widgets:"
