  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Verifying Project Success**\n\nI\'m pleased to report that `lint_applet` and `compile_applet` completed without errors. However, I\'ve paused to meticulously double-check our adherence to guidelines. Specifically, I\'ve confirmed that the unnamed app is now properly labeled \"Spotify Discovery Boost Review\" in `/metadata.json`. I am about to carefully re-examine the file structure to eliminate any oversight.\n\n\n**Confirming Compliance Checklist**\n\nI\'m checking if we met the criteria, and everything looks good! We didn\'t need custom API key UI or absolute paths. The logic is cleanly split across multiple files. Icons are imported from `lucide-react`, and Tailwind works as expected. The interactive elements fulfill user requests completely, with all features implemented as specified, including microcopy and rationale. I\'m pleased with how this is shaping up.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have successfully reviewed and optimized your **Spotify Discovery Boost** prototype, upgrading it from a raw draft into a high-fidelity, interactive, production-ready product evaluation sandbox and senior PM console. \n\nRather than merely listing critique bullet points in plain text, I have built a **fully interactive, responsive split-screen evaluation dashboard** in React + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS:\n1. **On the Left**: A high-fidelity, interactive **Spotify Player & Queue Phone Simulation** where you can switch in real-time between the **Raw Original Flow** (exhibiting the identified UX friction points) and the **Revised Production-Ready Flow** (showcasing all proposed improvements like interactive slider controls, organic prompts, and real-time algorithmic tuning).\n2. **On the Right**: A comprehensive, tabbed **Senior PM & UX Lead Review Console** that provides deep, strategic, and detailed critiques mapping directly to your ten evaluation parameters.\n3. **At the Bottom**: A live **Simulation Telemetry Log Terminal** that captures every tap, skip, like, opt-out, and feedback gesture you perform on the phone, immediately calculating the algorithmic state impact.\n\n---\n\n### Key Review & Critique Summary (PM & UX Perspectives)\n\nHere is a summary of the strategic, product, and interaction upgrades implemented across the application:\n\n#### 1. Strategic Verdict: Student Project vs. Real Spotify Feature\n*   **The Verdict**: The original draft feels like a **student concept** due to its heavy reliance on invasive interrupts and manual queue manipulation. In a real streaming app, a user\'s active queue is sacred ground (\"Queue Sovereignty\"). Forcing a pop-up and injecting items without direct consent is perceived as spammy or \"payola\" (paid placements).\n*   **The Pivot**: The **Revised Flow** re-engineers this into a quiet, consent-driven **\"Pull Model.\"** The interruptive dialog is replaced by a sleek, glowing organic nudge badge in the player, and we introduce a clear **Micro-Onboarding Settings Card** before any tracks are injected.\n\n#### 2. Overcoming UX Friction & Promoting Trust\n*   **The Problem**: Users are naturally skeptical of automatic recommendations. A plain `\342\234\250 New` tag does not help and increases frustration if the track is a mismatch.\n*   **The Solution**: We introduce the **Recommendation Rationale Capsule** (e.g., *\"Inspired by your love for M83\"*). By explicitly telling the user *why* a track is in their queue, skepticism is replaced by discovery curiosity. \n*   **Full Control Safety Valve**: We added an immediate **Revert Boost** button at the top of the queue. If a listener dislikes the matches, a single tap instantly sweeps away all injected songs, restoring their pristine queue.\n\n#### 3. Personalization Intensity Slider & Inline Tuning\n*   Our revised onboarding presents a **Boost Intensity Slider** allowing listeners to specify their discovery tolerance:\n    *   **Subtle Mode**: Blends only 1 track for every 5 songs (high comfort/focus orientation).\n    *   **Balanced Mode**: Blends 2 tracks for every 5 songs (optimal sweet spot).\n    *   **Adventurous Mode**: Blends 3+ tracks (maximum novelty exploration).\n*   **Immediate Feedback Loops**: Every discovery track in the queue is appended with real-time tuning pills: `Save Song`, `More Like This`, or `Skip Style` (which instantly swaps out the track for another candidate in real-time).\n\n#### 4. Premium Microcopy Revisions\nWe moved away from shaming repetitive behavior (*\"enjoying the same tracks...\"*) toward celebrating their signature tastes:\n*   **Before (Prompt Title)**: *\342\200\234You\342\200\231ve been enjoying the same tracks lately.\342\200\235*\n*   **After (Spotify Grade)**: *\342\200\234Want to refresh your session?\342\200\235*\n*   **Before (CTA)**: *\342\200\234Try Discovery Boost\342\200\235*\n*   **After (Spotify Grade)**: *\342\200\234Boost This Session\342\200\235* (Localizes commitment to the current listening hour).\n*   **Before (Track tag)**: *\342\200\234\342\234\250 New\342\200\235*\n*   **After (Spotify Grade)**: *\342\200\234\342\234\250 Discovery Match\342\200\235*\n\n#### 5. Recommended Launch KPIs & Telemetry Metrics\nIn the review console, you can interact with a live simulated metrics board tracking:\n1.  **Discovery Session Retention (42.6%)**: Rate of users keeping the blend active across consecutive sessions.\n2.  **Skip-to-Like Ratio (2.3x)**: The optimal skip-to-save ratio to measure algorithmic acoustic matching precision.\n3.  **Boost Bounce Rate (4.8%)**: Percentage of users disabling the boost within 5 minutes (the primary indicator of taste mismatch).\n4.  **Library Addition Rate (18.7%)**: Success rate of boosted tracks transitioning into permanent \"Liked Songs.\"\n\n---\n\n### Implemented End-to-End User Flow\n\n1.  **Repetitive Loop Detection**: System quietly triggers a flashing, organic `REFRESH` notification badge in the active player (non-disruptive).\n2.  **Micro-Onboarding**: User taps the badge to open a custom bottom-sheet explaining the rules of the blend, featuring the **Intensity Selector**.\n3.  **Smart Queue Slotting**: Tracks are injected at spaced intervals, clearly labeled with their **Acoustic Rationale** (e.g., *\"Matches the upbeat synth of MGMT\"*).\n4.  **In-Line Refinement**: User can tune parameters, skip style alternatives, or completely clear the boost at any point inside the queue list.\n5.  **Celebration Overlay**: Liking an injected track triggers a premium, immersive haptic vector **Heart Burst** celebration, feeding positive reinforcement back to the backend recommendation weights.\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 1
      nanos: 986896785
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
